The paper deals with information-theoretic security and cryptography, which are typically covered under the sub-categories of cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also involves the use of channels and protocols, which could fall under cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Additionally, the paper introduces a novel use of interactive hashing, which could be relevant to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
